description:
File: lichen/subsys/lichen/meshtastic/codec.c:477-511

  static const char *info_firmware_version(
      const struct lichen_meshtastic_local_info *info)
  {
      const char *version = (info != NULL) ? info->firmware_version : NULL;
      ...
      return info->firmware_version;  // Returns the pointer from caller's struct
  }

The function returns either a static string literal (the default) or info->firmware_version directly.

If the caller's info struct or its firmware_version string is freed/modified after this function returns but before the returned pointer is used, this leads to use-after-free or data corruption.

The encoding functions that call this (lichen_meshtastic_encode_metadata_payload at line 870) encode immediately, so this is likely safe in current usage.

SECURITY: Document that returned pointer is only valid while info struct and its strings are valid.
